  "text": "Urethritis caused by Neisseria gonorrhea can affect fertility only if the testes were affected in rare situations. After the human immunodeficiency virus (HIV) epidemic in Western countries, more sexual precautions and hygiene were adopted, and this lead to marked decrease in the incidence of N. gonorrhea infection in the male genital tract [CITATION_1] .",
